.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-1-7::.
City: prague, hamburg, new-york, berlin, venice, london
The people use 6 different means of transport: bike, motorbike, roller, ship, snowmobile, trike
1. the person traveling to prague is on the right of the person traveling to venice##1
2. the person driving the snowmobile is on the right of the person traveling to hamburg##1
3. the person traveling to new-york is on the left of the person driving the bike##1
4. the person traveling to berlin is on the left of the person driving the roller##1
5. the person traveling to berlin is the person driving the trike##1
6. the person traveling to new-york is the person driving the roller##1
7. the person driving the bike is on the left of the person driving the ship##1
8. the person traveling to hamburg is on the far left##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1     |     2      |   3   |     4      |   5   |     6      |
| City         | hamburg       | london     | berlin | new-york | venice | prague |
| Transport   | motorbike | snowmobile | trike | roller     | bike  | ship       |

